</h3><h3 tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-kHOZwM hRBLBR pf-79_">Temperature</h3><p class="sc-hOGkXu hVdrsp pf-81_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Temperature is a crucial indicator of infection or other health conditions. Normal body temperature ranges from 36.5°C to 37.5°C.
</p><h3 tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-kHOZwM hRBLBR pf-83_">Pulse</h3><p class="sc-hOGkXu hVdrsp pf-85_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">The heartbeat rate, typically between 60 to 100 beats per minute, can indicate heart health, stress levels, and other conditions.
</p><h3 tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-kHOZwM hRBLBR pf-87_">Blood pressure
</h3><p class="sc-hOGkXu hVdrsp pf-89_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Reflecting the force of blood against artery walls, normal blood pressure is usually around 120/80 mmHg.
</p><h3 tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-kHOZwM hRBLBR pf-91_">Respiratory rate
</h3><p class="sc-hOGkXu hVdrsp pf-93_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">The rate of breathing, with a normal range of 12 to 20 breaths per minute, can signal respiratory or cardiac issues.
</p><h3 tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-kHOZwM hRBLBR pf-95_">Oxygen saturation
</h3><p class="sc-hOGkXu hVdrsp pf-97_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">The oxygen level in the blood, with a normal saturation level above 95%, indicates how well oxygen is being transported to the extremities.
