</p></div></div><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:6;--c-md:6;--c-lg:6"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fHeRUh cCunWv pf-160_"><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/10_14c81480-3bed-43ae-b305-affea403ba6c.png?v=1709569275" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/10_14c81480-3bed-43ae-b305-affea403ba6c.png?v=1709569275 1536w" width="1966" height="1311" alt="Achieving Compliance Excellence: Healthcare Regulatory Compliance and Clinical Observation Policy - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="Achieving Compliance Excellence: Healthcare Regulatory Compliance and Clinical Observation Policy - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-fbyfCU cCdixN pf-161_"/><p class="sc-hOGkXu hVdrsp pf-162_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Image by Wavebreakmedia via Envato Elements</p></div></div></div></div></div><div data-section-id="pf-243f" data-pf-type="Section" class="sc-uojGG hMqLeX pf-164_ pf-lg-hide pf-md-hide pf-sm-hide"><div style="--cw:1170px" class="sc-ilfuhL bpQaoh"><div class="sc-furwcr dAWGlU pf-165_ pf-r pf-c-cm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fHeRUh cCunWv pf-166_"><p class="sc-hOGkXu hVdrsp pf-167_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3"><a href="https://www.mandatorytraining.co.uk/pages/dr-richard-dune-blog" target="_blank"></a>Clinical observations are the bedrock of patient care in health and social care settings. These observations, crucial for monitoring a patient's health status, offer invaluable insights that guide healthcare professionals in making informed decisions.
<br><br>In this blog, <i><a href="https://www.mandatorytraining.co.uk/pages/dr-richard-dune-blog" target="_blank"><span style="color: rgb(74, 144, 226);">Dr Richard Dune</span></a></i>&nbsp;delves into the essence of clinical observations within UK health and social care settings, exploring their significance, the vital signs monitored, and the best practices ensuring high-quality care delivery.
</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-furwcr dAWGlU pf-169_ pf-r pf-c-cm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fHeRUh cCunWv pf-170_"><h3 tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-kHOZwM hRBLBR pf-171_">The importance of clinical observations
</h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/2_d7663ce5-a607-415e-8606-f16ffcf8bfaa.png?v=1709569275" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/2_d7663ce5-a607-415e-8606-f16ffcf8bfaa.png?v=1709569275 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/2_d7663ce5-a607-415e-8606-f16ffcf8bfaa_1500x.png?v=1709569275 1280w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/2_d7663ce5-a607-415e-8606-f16ffcf8bfaa_1000x.png?v=1709569275 768w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/2_d7663ce5-a607-415e-8606-f16ffcf8bfaa_500x.png?v=1709569275 320w" width="1653" height="1233" alt="Mastering Foundations of Clinical Observations: Vital Signs Assessment and Patient Monitoring Techniques - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="Mastering Foundations of Clinical Observations: Vital Signs Assessment and Patient Monitoring Techniques - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-fbyfCU cCdixN pf-176_"/><p class="sc-hOGkXu hVdrsp pf-177_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Image by YuriArcursPeopleimages via Envato Elements</p><p class="sc-hOGkXu hVdrsp pf-173_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Clinical observations are fundamental in healthcare for several reasons. They are the first step in the assessment process, helping to identify potential health issues before they become critical. In the UK, where the healthcare system is under increasing pressure, the ability to quickly and accurately assess a patient's condition can be the difference between recovery and deterioration.
</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-furwcr dAWGlU pf-179_ pf-r pf-c-cm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fHeRUh cCunWv pf-180_"><h3 tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-kHOZwM hRBLBR pf-181_">Key facts and statistics
</h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/3_c3632d79-c1cd-49c5-a65b-70c67e2a8ed7.png?v=1709569275" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/3_c3632d79-c1cd-49c5-a65b-70c67e2a8ed7.png?v=1709569275 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/3_c3632d79-c1cd-49c5-a65b-70c67e2a8ed7_1000x.png?v=1709569275 768w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/3_c3632d79-c1cd-49c5-a65b-70c67e2a8ed7_500x.png?v=1709569275 320w" width="1382" height="922" alt="Elevate Healthcare Observation Skills: Clinical Observation Training and Best Practices - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="Elevate Healthcare Observation Skills: Clinical Observation Training and Best Practices - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-fbyfCU cCdixN pf-183_"/><p class="sc-hOGkXu hVdrsp pf-184_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Image by Prostock-studio&nbsp;via Envato Elements</p><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-kYHfwS lkFAWj pf-186_"><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-xiLah cpQDEO pf-187_">Early detection of patient deterioration through clinical observations can reduce ICU admissions by up to 30%.
</li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-xiLah cpQDEO pf-189_">Accurate clinical observations are associated with a significant reduction in hospital mortality rates.
</li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-xiLah cpQDEO pf-191_">Over 60,000 patients annually deteriorate in UK hospital wards to the extent that they require ICU admission. Late or missed recognition of deterioration is associated with worse patient outcomes, including higher mortality (Pimentel et al. 2021).
</li></ul></div></div></div><div class="sc-furwcr dAWGlU pf-193_ pf-r pf-c-cm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fHeRUh cCunWv pf-194_"><h3 tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-kHOZwM hRBLBR pf-195_">Key definitions
</h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/4_58937eb5-3cb6-4e7b-b31e-e97c33dac0dd.png?v=1709569275" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/4_58937eb5-3cb6-4e7b-b31e-e97c33dac0dd.png?v=1709569275 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/4_58937eb5-3cb6-4e7b-b31e-e97c33dac0dd_1500x.png?v=1709569275 1280w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/4_58937eb5-3cb6-4e7b-b31e-e97c33dac0dd_1000x.png?v=1709569275 768w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/4_58937eb5-3cb6-4e7b-b31e-e97c33dac0dd_500x.png?v=1709569275 320w" width="1981" height="1321" alt="Implementing Early Warning Score System: Ensuring Patient Safety Standards - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="Implementing Early Warning Score System: Ensuring Patient Safety Standards - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-fbyfCU cCdixN pf-197_"/><p class="sc-hOGkXu hVdrsp pf-198_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Image by mstandret

 via Envato Elements</p><h3 tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-kHOZwM hRBLBR pf-200_">Vital signs
</h3><p class="sc-hOGkXu hVdrsp pf-202_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Vital signs are the primary indicators of physiological status, including temperature, pulse, blood pressure, respiratory rate, and oxygen saturation.
</p><h3 tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-kHOZwM hRBLBR pf-204_">Clinical observations
</h3><p class="sc-hOGkXu hVdrsp pf-206_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Clinical observations relate to the process of monitoring, recording, and interpreting vital signs to assess a patient's health status.
</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-furwcr dAWGlU pf-208_ pf-r pf-c-cm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fHeRUh cCunWv pf-209_"><h3 tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-kHOZwM hRBLBR pf-210_">Relevant legislation, regulations, and best practice
</h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/5_104912fd-7ca9-4781-8cee-b2aa96fe1a5a.png?v=1709569275" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/5_104912fd-7ca9-4781-8cee-b2aa96fe1a5a.png?v=1709569275 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/5_104912fd-7ca9-4781-8cee-b2aa96fe1a5a_1000x.png?v=1709569275 768w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/5_104912fd-7ca9-4781-8cee-b2aa96fe1a5a_500x.png?v=1709569275 320w" width="1475" height="829" alt="Navigating Clinical Observation Policy: Compliance Training and Accredited Courses - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="Navigating Clinical Observation Policy: Compliance Training and Accredited Courses - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-fbyfCU cCdixN pf-212_"/><p class="sc-hOGkXu hVdrsp pf-213_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Image by  DC_Studio via Envato Elements</p><p class="sc-hOGkXu hVdrsp pf-215_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">In the UK, clinical observations are governed by a framework that includes the Health and Social Care Act 2008, Care Quality Commission (CQC) standards, and National Institute for Health and Care Excellence (NICE) guidelines. These regulations ensure that clinical observations are performed to a high standard, safeguarding patient safety and care quality.
</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-furwcr dAWGlU pf-217_ pf-r pf-c-cm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fHeRUh cCunWv pf-218_"><h3 tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-kHOZwM hRBLBR pf-219_">The vital signs
</h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/6_0bd7bed1-4bad-4698-9d0e-d5f38f182c35.png?v=1709569275" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/6_0bd7bed1-4bad-4698-9d0e-d5f38f182c35.png?v=1709569275 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/6_0bd7bed1-4bad-4698-9d0e-d5f38f182c35_1500x.png?v=1709569275 1280w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/6_0bd7bed1-4bad-4698-9d0e-d5f38f182c35_1000x.png?v=1709569275 768w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/6_0bd7bed1-4bad-4698-9d0e-d5f38f182c35_500x.png?v=1709569275 320w" width="1624" height="2066" alt="Enhancing Healthcare Quality: Clinical Observation Best Practices and Accredited Training - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="Enhancing Healthcare Quality: Clinical Observation Best Practices and Accredited Training - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-fbyfCU cCdixN pf-221_"/><p class="sc-hOGkXu hVdrsp pf-222_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Image by kapitilka via Envato Elements</p><h3 tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-kHOZwM hRBLBR pf-224_">Temperature</h3><p class="sc-hOGkXu hVdrsp pf-226_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Temperature is a crucial indicator of infection or other health conditions. Normal body temperature ranges from 36.5°C to 37.5°C.
</p><h3 tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-kHOZwM hRBLBR pf-228_">Pulse</h3><p class="sc-hOGkXu hVdrsp pf-230_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">The heartbeat rate, typically between 60 to 100 beats per minute, can indicate heart health, stress levels, and other conditions.
</p><h3 tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-kHOZwM hRBLBR pf-232_">Blood pressure
</h3><p class="sc-hOGkXu hVdrsp pf-234_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Reflecting the force of blood against artery walls, normal blood pressure is usually around 120/80 mmHg.
</p><h3 tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-kHOZwM hRBLBR pf-236_">Respiratory rate
</h3><p class="sc-hOGkXu hVdrsp pf-238_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">The rate of breathing, with a normal range of 12 to 20 breaths per minute, can signal respiratory or cardiac issues.
</p><h3 tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-kHOZwM hRBLBR pf-240_">Oxygen saturation
</h3><p class="sc-hOGkXu hVdrsp pf-242_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">The oxygen level in the blood, with a normal saturation level above 95%, indicates how well oxygen is being transported to the extremities.
</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-furwcr dAWGlU pf-244_ pf-r pf-c-cm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fHeRUh cCunWv pf-245_"><h3 tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-kHOZwM hRBLBR pf-246_">Role in diagnosing and monitoring
</h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/7_7982f86a-8f81-49de-8a01-57633bba29fd.png?v=1709569275" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/7_7982f86a-8f81-49de-8a01-57633bba29fd.png?v=1709569275 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/7_7982f86a-8f81-49de-8a01-57633bba29fd_1500x.png?v=1709569275 1280w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/7_7982f86a-8f81-49de-8a01-57633bba29fd_1000x.png?v=1709569275 768w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/7_7982f86a-8f81-49de-8a01-57633bba29fd_500x.png?v=1709569275 320w" width="1672" height="1115" alt="Empower Professional Development: Clinical Observation Courses and CPD - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="Empower Professional Development: Clinical Observation Courses and CPD - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-fbyfCU cCdixN pf-248_"/><p class="sc-hOGkXu hVdrsp pf-249_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Image by FoToArtist_1 via Envato Elements</p><p class="sc-hOGkXu hVdrsp pf-251_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Clinical observations are pivotal in diagnosing and monitoring patients. They provide the first clues to a patient's condition, guiding further diagnostic testing and treatment. For example, a spike in temperature can indicate an infection requiring prompt intervention.
</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-furwcr dAWGlU pf-253_ pf-r pf-c-cm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fHeRUh cCunWv pf-254_"><h3 tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-kHOZwM hRBLBR pf-255_">Best practices for performing clinical observations
</h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/8_cdd36e71-f596-472c-9b8a-d5a5a275f5d0.png?v=1709569275" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/8_cdd36e71-f596-472c-9b8a-d5a5a275f5d0.png?v=1709569275 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/8_cdd36e71-f596-472c-9b8a-d5a5a275f5d0_500x.png?v=1709569275 320w" width="889" height="1334" alt="Leading with Clinical Observation Accredited Courses: NICE Guidelines and CQC Standards - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="Leading with Clinical Observation Accredited Courses: NICE Guidelines and CQC Standards - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-fbyfCU cCdixN pf-257_"/><p class="sc-hOGkXu hVdrsp pf-258_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Image by DC_Studio via Envato Elements</p><h3 tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-kHOZwM hRBLBR pf-260_">Consistency and accuracy
</h3><p class="sc-hOGkXu hVdrsp pf-262_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Use standardised equipment and techniques to ensure reliable measurements.
</p><h3 tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-kHOZwM hRBLBR pf-264_">Timely and regular assessments
</h3><p class="sc-hOGkXu hVdrsp pf-266_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Perform observations at regular intervals or more frequently for patients at risk.
</p><h3 tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-kHOZwM hRBLBR pf-268_">Comprehensive training
</h3><p class="sc-hOGkXu hVdrsp pf-270_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Ensure all healthcare professionals are trained in the latest clinical observation techniques.
</p><h3 tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-kHOZwM hRBLBR pf-272_">Patient-centered approach
</h3><p class="sc-hOGkXu hVdrsp pf-274_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Tailor observations to patients' individual needs, considering their comfort and dignity.
</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-furwcr dAWGlU pf-276_ pf-r pf-c-cm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fHeRUh cCunWv pf-277_"><h3 tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-kHOZwM hRBLBR pf-278_">Recommendations
</h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/9_867cd198-e984-4c13-ac9a-6ffc386d1403.png?v=1709569275" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/9_867cd198-e984-4c13-ac9a-6ffc386d1403.png?v=1709569275 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/9_867cd198-e984-4c13-ac9a-6ffc386d1403_1000x.png?v=1709569275 768w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/9_867cd198-e984-4c13-ac9a-6ffc386d1403_500x.png?v=1709569275 320w" width="1334" height="889" alt="Excelling in Vital Signs Monitoring: Clinical Observation Training and Accredited Courses - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="Excelling in Vital Signs Monitoring: Clinical Observation Training and Accredited Courses - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-fbyfCU cCdixN pf-280_"/><p class="sc-hOGkXu hVdrsp pf-281_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Image by DC_Studio via Envato Elements</p><p class="sc-hOGkXu hVdrsp pf-283_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">To enhance the effectiveness of clinical observations in health and social care settings, healthcare providers should:
</p><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-kYHfwS lkFAWj pf-285_"><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-xiLah cpQDEO pf-286_">Adopt the latest technology and equipment for more accurate and efficient observations.
